  "text": "The SWH is equivalent to the average of the highest one-third of waves in a sea state, corresponding to what an experienced sailor would report to characterize the wave height. The SWH is computed as four times the squareroot of the 0-order spectral moment, with the directional wave spectra being calculated by the ERA-40 wave model. According to Ref. [CITATION_1] , among the caveats of the ERA-40 SWH data presented in the KNMI wave atlas is the fact that the estimates are based on data averaged on a 1.5",
